Package fr.emse.simulator.world

This package contains interfaces for the simulation domain: a map containing cells that may be occupied by occupants.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Cell
    A cell is a component of a map.
    Coin
    This interface is used to represent coins.
    Occupant
    An Occupant is an object that can occupy a Cell.
    Robber
    This interface is used to represent a robber.
    Robot
    This interface is used to represent a robot.
    SimulationMap
    This interface is the type used by a MapFrame to graphically display a map.
    Wall
    This interface is used to represent a wall.

Package fr.emse.simulator.world Description

This package contains interfaces for the simulation domain: a map containing cells that may be occupied by occupants. Several entities can be represented: box, intruder, robot and wall.
